| {{flag|Japan}}
| [[Tokyo]]
| {{sort|2017-08-30|30 August – 1 September}}
| May traveled to Japan to improve relations with the country and discuss a potential new UK-Japan trade agreement for the period after [[Brexit]] concludes.<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/theresa-may-japan-visit-brexit-trade-british-business-leave-eu-uk-north-korea-a7919456.html</ref>  Her visit also involved discussions surrounding threats which [[List of North Korean missile tests|North Korea's nuclear missile tests]] posed to Japan.<ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41088404</ref>  She met with, among others, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe.<ref>https://www.cnbc.com/2017/08/31/theresa-may-is-in-japan-to-talk-trade-but-she-cant-give-tokyo-what-it-really-wants.html</ref> and Emperor Akihito.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41122792</ref> During a joint press conference in Tokyo, Abe and May pledged agreement to a new economic deal between both Britain and Japan, as well as British and Japanese companies, which would in the future expand on the current EU-Japan deal following the completion of Brexit.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/aug/31/theresa-may-secures-japanese-pledge-on-post-brexit-trade-deal</ref><ref>https://www.ft.com/content/594db41e-8f18-11e7-a352-e46f43c5825d</ref>
